## 8. Conventions

### i18n
- Use `useKubevirtTranslation` hook
- All user-facing strings must be translated
- Run `npm run i18n` after adding strings

### Styling
- Use PatternFly components and variables (tokens)
- Prefer PatternFly components for layouts (Flex, Stack, Grid, Split, ...)
- Use PatternFly utility classes
- SCSS with BEM methodology
- Don't rely on PatternFly class names in SCSS files

### Error Handling
- Always handle loading, error, empty states
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors for debugging

### Testing
- Unit tests for hooks and utilities
- Playwright E2E tests for critical user flows (new tests in `playwright/tests/scenario/`)
- Cypress E2E tests (legacy)
- Use `data-test` attributes for UI automation selectors (kebab-case values)
- In Playwright, use `this.testId('id')` to locate elements by `data-test`
